review: This is still the best Counter Strike I dont know why this one isnt free and day of defeat

Yes, yes, YES. I finally got the game for myself. I grinded a lot but I eventually bought it. Oh boy where should I start. Ah yes the...

1. Gameplay

This game is from 2004 and suprisingly the gameplay improved very much. Like a LOT. going from a very percise shots to more realistic shot was a big Improvement. Before I bought this game I did some research (unlike whit Dead by Daylike) and after looking at pros destroy pretty much everyone I decided It was something for me. The first game I played in the franchise was CS:GO(Counter Strike: Global Offensiv. Its free on steam so you can also try it out). I like it but my potato Laptop couldnt handle it very much. I then began researching about what other CS games are out there and then I came to the decision that I will buy Counter Strike: Source (CSS from now on). I liked the gameplay, the weapons, the graphics (especialy my laptop) and the physiks of this now almost 2 decade old game. 

2. Multiplayer
I always wanted to play competitivly on any game (exept Dead by Daylight) but my potatoe couldnt handle the Ultr4 g!Ga m3gA graphics. So since my life regret (Dead by Daylight) I began playing older games like Dark Souls, Bioshock, Fallout 3/NV, CS 1.6/CZ (Condition Zero) and many more games. The only "weird" thing about is that you can also grind achievments in offline mode (whit bots). Thats the only weird thing I found about this game. Now I may have 4 hours of playtime at the time I am writing this but I do know that this games is near perfection. There is no campain if your courius (just like in all the other CS games out there. I pointed this out just for those who are looking for a good CS game and not really knowing much about the franchise). I just grindid my way to a rare achievment whit players of course because, if you ply whit bots you will just get worse and worse. I learned that leason the hard way. Trust me on that one. So yeah. I currently have 32/147! achievments so I still got a lot to play. If your an achievment hunter, this is the game for you.

3. Community
Now I dont really like talking that much whit stangers online because I am an introvert ultra pro max. But there might be some arseholes on the game who might have had a rough day and just want to take it out on some newb or player. Those people are like playong since day 1 so they might get pissed of if they ever get killed or backstabed. Just ignore them.

Now enough writing. If you just skipped to this bit then your at the wrong place but if you want a short sentance about how I personally feel about the game then here it is: Hell yeah! Take my money you bastards. 
Now thank you for reading my review. Hope it helped you out. If it did then give me a thumbs up or just leave a quick comment on how you personally feel about this game or just let me know if this review helped you out. Oh yeah, and one more thing. The community on CSS is getting smaller (atleast here in the EU). So please, PLEASE support the creators and make this community alive again. I dont know who is going to read this in 2020 but here it is. Have yourself a nice day/night
Good bye

This is going to be my first review of a game on my steam account, I will make all my reviews after I have invested at least 20 hours in a game. I will give my honest opinion.

So, CSS.  I picked this game up early in my gaming career when I started out playing games on a dell d630.  At the lowest settings this game looks about the same as cranking the graphics up to high.  Most of the hours I spent in this game was playing with bots on car rides and journeys. I enjoy the gunplay and the weapons are not as in depth compared to its bigger brother.  The maps are very well designed and I didnt find a single one I absolutely hated. What makes me like this game over its bigger brother is the lesser competitive feel. You can definitely tell that CSGO was designed from the ground up to be a highly competitive game.  However that is not what I look for in a game. I tend to focus on how much fun I have had with a game. Now it might be my nostalgia from playing this at 30fps at 480p but I still think this is the game to pick up if you are looking for a fun, brief round of shooty fun.

Tercera entrega de la saga Counter Strike .
Despues del mitico Counter Strike 1.6 y el Nefasto Condition Zero nos llego esta tercera parte de la saga Counter Strike.

Counter-Strike: Source (CS:S) es un videojuego de la serie Counter-Strike. Al igual que sus predecesores, es un juego de estilo FPS (First Person Shooter) y fue lanzado al mercado el 7 de octubre de 2004. Se diferencia principalmente de sus antecesores ya que utiliza un nuevo motor de videojuego conocido como Source (el mismo que utiliza Half-Life 2), el cual es m√°s potente y posee gr√°ficos mejorados, admitiendo por primera vez en la serie de efectos como Normal mapping, reflejos y HDR; tambi√©n utiliza el motor f√≠sico Havok, que hace que efectos f√≠sicos como ragdolls y detecci√≥n de colisi√≥n compleja (en lugar de usar cajas de colisi√≥n se usan pol√≠gonos) sean posibles.

Puntos Positivos
-Gran mejora grafica respecto a Counter Strike 1.6 o Condition Zero
-Muy buena IA y fisicas
-Se mantenio en la jugabilidad y escenarios bastante fiel al Counter strike 1.6.

This is an old story about a friend i met in css, if you got time to read it, feel free - Thanks

There was once a guy i met in a normal game. I played versus him. We had quite some fun, i won the game after a while, his teammates flamed him in all chat to report him, but he seemed very friendly and just overall a good guy. So i've added him after the match and we talked a bit. It shocked me what he told me. This guy, went through so much that i didn't even know what to say. Since he was a kid, his family told him that he is trash, that he is useless and he would never achieve anything in life, that he only brings trouble to the family and why he doesn't kill himself already. His parents also were very violent and hit him almost daily. He had no friends, nothing in life worth for living. He tried suicide but failed and went into some kinda hospital (which i forgot) for some months. He took medicine against his depressions, which didn't help him at all. He also took overdosis once. This boy is the nicest person i have ever met and the fact that he had to go through such things, it just made me sick. So after the time he told me everything, which took a while cause he was very shy, i tried to help him with every little bit i had. Since myself had a hard time at that moment, i just could relate to him even more. All he did every day was laying in bed, listening to music and playing css. It was not easy for me to help him since he was already in such deep depression for years.
I don't know what happened exactly happend cause we didn't play together these last days, but man he got really upset. He wrote me a message with the words that he is quitting css and will kill himself. I tried to contact him but till now i got no response. I know him well enough to know that he wouldn't joke about such things, but i don't know what to think or feel now. Everytime i play css i think about him and what happend to him.

I'm sorry i couldn't help you more Gabriel. I miss you and will never forget you. Wherever you are, just know that i will go the path for both of us. You have helped me more then you think and i thank you so much for the time we had together.

God Bless

I recently started to play CS:S again and I switch from CS:GO to CS:S from time to time depending on my mood for that moment. The first very important thing that came up to my mind was how friendly the community still is. In CS:GO I rarely join a server where people just play their game and have fun in a joyful harmony with a friendly atmosphere. No salt, no toxicity. I recently played many hours and nobody was calling others noobs or were insulting anyone whereas in CS:GO even on simple Deathmatch servers there are these toxic kids in delayed puberty judging everyones gameplay without any provocation. Then you have these blatant cheaters even in casual mode, joining especially at nights to wallbang ace every round just for the trolling fun of it.
Seems like the real CS community, where people only bother about having fun, no ranks, no skins, with cizilized behavior is in the servers of the good old CS 1.6 and CS:S servers. Awesome people.

„ÄäToday I begin a new life„Äã

„ÄÄ„ÄÄToday I shed my old skin which hath, too long, suffered the bruises of failure and the wounds of mediority.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄToday I am born anew and my birthplace is a vineyard where there is fruit for all.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄToday I will pluck grapes of wisdom from the tallest and fullest vines in the vineyard,for these were planted by the wisest of my profession who have come before me,generation upon generation.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄToday I will savor the taste of grapes from these vines and verily I will swallow the seed of success buried in each and new life will sprout within me.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄThe career I have chosen is laden with opportunity yet it is fraught with heartbreak and despair and the bodies of those who have failed, were they piled one atop another, would cast a shadow down upon all the pyramids of the earth.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄYet I will not fail, as the others, for in my hands I now hold the charts which will guide through perilous waters to shores which only yesterday seemed but a dream.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄFailure no longer will be my payment for struggle. Just as nature made no provision for my body to tolerate pain neither has it made any provision for my life to suffer failure. Failure, like pain, is alien to my life. In the past I accepted it as I accepted pain. Now I reject it and I am prepared for wisdom and principles which will guide me out of the shadows into the sunlight of wealth, position, and happiness far beyond my most extravagant dreams until even the golden apples in the Garden of Hesperides will seem no more than my just reward.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄTime teaches all things to him who lives forever but I have not the luxury of eternity. Yet within my allotted time I must practice the art of patience for nature acts never in haste. To create the olive, king of all trees, a hundred years is required. An onion plant is old in nine weeks. I have lived as an onion plant. It has not pleased me. Now I wouldst become the greatest of olive trees and, in truth, the greatest of salesman.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄAnd how will this be accomplished? For I have neither the knowledge nor the experience to achieve the greatness and already I have stumbled in ignorance and fallen into pools of self-pity. The answer is simple. I will commence my journey unencumbered with either the weight of unnecessary knowledge or the handicap of meaningless experience. Nature already has supplied me with knowledge and instinct far greater than any beast in the forest and the value of experience is overrated, usually by old men who nod wisely and speak stupidly.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄIn truth, experience teaches thoroughly yet her course of instruction devours men's years so the value of her lessons diminishes with the time necessary to acquire her special wisdom. The end finds it wasted on dead men. Furthermore, experience is comparable to fashion; an action that proved successful today will be unworkable and impractical tomorrow.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄOnly principles endure and these I now possess, for the laws that will lead me to greatness are contained in the words of these scrolls. What they will teach me is more to prevent failure than to gain success, for what is success other than a state of mind? Which two, among a thouand wise men, will define success in the same words; yet failure is always described but one way. Failure is man's inability to reach his goals in life, whatever they may be.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄIn truth, the only difference between those who have failed and those who have successed lies in the difference of their habits. Good habits are the key to all success. Bad habits are the unlocked door to failure. Thus, the first law I will obey, which precedeth all others is --I will form good habits and become their slave.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄAs a child I was slave to my impulses; now I am slave to my habits, as are all grown men. I have surrendered my free will to the years of accumulated habits and the past deeds of my life have already marked out a path which threatens to imprison my future. My actions are ruled by appetite, passion, prejudice, greed, love, fear, environment, habit, and the worst of these tyrants is habit. Therefore, if I must be a slave to habit let me be a slave to good habits. My bad habits must be destroyed and new furrows prepared for good seed.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄI will form good habits and become their slave.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄAnd how will I accomplish this difficult feat? Through these scrolls, it will be done, for each scroll contains a principle which will drive a bad habit from my life and replace it with one which will bring me closer to success. For it is another of nature's laws that only a habit can subdue another habit. So, in order for these written words to perform their chosen task, I must discipline myself with the first of my new habits which is as follows:

„ÄÄ„ÄÄI will read each scroll for thirty days in this prescribed manner, before I proceed to the next scroll.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄFirst, I will read the words in silence when I arise. Then, I will read the words in silence after I have partaken of my midday meal. Last, I will read the words again just before I retire at day's end, and most important, on this occasion I will read the words aloud.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄOn the next day I will repeat this procedure, and I will continue in like manner for thirty days. Then, I will turn to the next scroll and repeat this procedure for another thirty days. I will continue in this manner until I have lived with each scroll for thirty days and my reading has become habit.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄAnd what will be accomplished with this habit? Herein lies the hidden secret of all man's accomplishments. As I repeat the words daily they will soon become a part of my active mind, but more important, they will also seep into my other mind, that mysterious source which never sleeps, which creates my dreams, and often makes me act in ways I do not comprehend.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄAs the words of these scrolls are consumed by my mysterious mind I will begin to awake, each morning, with a vitality I have never known before. My vigor will increase, my enthusiasm will rise, my desire to meet the world will overcome every fear I once knew at sunrise, and I will be happier than I ever believed it possible to be in this world of strife and sorrow.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄEventually I will find myself reacting to all situations which confront me as I was commanded in the scrolls to react, and soon these actions and reactions will become easy to perform, for any act with practice becomes easy.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄThus a new and good habit is born, for when an act becomes easy through constant repetiton it becomes a pleasure to perform and if it is a pleasure to perform it is man's nature to perform it often. When I perform it often it becomes a habit and I become its slave and since it is a good habit this is my will.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄToday I begin a new life.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄAnd I make a solemn oath to myself that nothing will retard my new life's growth. I will lose not a day from these readings for that day cannot be retrieved nor can I substitute another for it. I must not , I will not, break this habit of daily reading from these scrolls and, in truth, the few moments spent each day on this new habit are but a small price to pay for the happiness and success that will be mine.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄAs I read and re-read the words in the scrolls to follow, never will I allow the brevity of each scroll nor the simplicity of its words to cause me to treat the scroll's message lightly. Thousands of grapes are pressed to fill one jar with wine, and the grapeskin and pulp are tossed to the birds. So it is with these grapes of wisdom from the ages. Much has been filtered and tossed to the wind.Only the pure truth lies distilled in the words to come. I will drink as instructed and spill not a drop. And the seed of success I will swallow.

„ÄÄ„ÄÄToday my old skin has become as dust. I will walk tall among men and they will know me not , for today I am a new man, with a new life.

Whoo, CSS, my favorite of the series.

I'll have to say, its gunplay is probably the best out of them.

It's just Counter-Strike with the Source engine, the only difference is that some maps from 1.6 didn't make it in and there are some new maps (that also happen to have not been carried over to GO.)


Both the new ones and the old ones have great map design, however. Bot AI is alright. They're still kinda stupid even in Hard but I can't complain too much since I'm pretty sure the AI was carried over from CZ (Condition Zero). What makes them harder is their boosted reaction times, weapon preferences, etc.


Speaking of bots, if you want to play with human players, there's no such thing as matchmaking or whatever, just a server browser which makes things...quite hard. Why? Oh, I dunno, could be UT2k4 sounds that are so repetitive that could stop you from playing on that server. Or maybe the fact that a server has 16k dollars whenever anyone spawns regardless of how many wins and losses. Basically, there is no tag for avoiding "community" servers. Which is exactly why I don't play this game online much. Also because literally every Brazilian player is some kind of insane pro that once he snags an M4 or AK you're screwed.


Sound design...eh...I mean, most of it was carried over from 1.6 and for its time, 1.6's sound design was actually pretty good. In 2004?...Not so much. I mean, it's still well-designed for detecting enemies and the like, but I mean the quality of the sounds. It all feels like someone just edited stock sounds to make it about enough to be used in gameplay.


The design for the weapons, the least important thing ever, since you can also just download a skin that at least makes it look better...For a Source remake, I'm actually impressed they managed to make the guns look like their real life selves in 2004! But if you're unhappy you can just do what I said above. (Some) reloading animations are so wrong, though. Then again the animations were from the original CS and back then Valve didn't actually own the IP. Ah, well. Reanimations can fix that, too.


Hitboxes are actually spot-on, unlike GO. You have an AK and your crosshair's on someone's head. What happens? Exactly.

Gameplay is balanced since its all carried over from 1.6.


I won't cover the radio chatter since that's more for practical reasons rather than flavor. If you're wondering why the voice acting on them's so lame, it's exactly because it's one of the higher staff from the original CS dev team doing the acting.

I'm also not going to criticize weapons I dislike despite them having a place in the game like everyone else. I hate the P90 and how overused it is, but if it's in the game, it's in the game. All of the weapons have their strengths and weaknesses.


Speaking of weapons, the 3-round burst is overpowered but I love it because of just that. It has pinpoint accuracy when firing, unlike 1.6 or literally every CS title as of yet, and it makes the AK seem like an untamed beast to use when you have the FAMAS' burst on someone's head. Literally 2 shots on one's head to get a headshot if they're wearing a helmet. You don't have to worry about the FAMAS missing one of those shots. The glock gets the same burst but it's not as effective, granted, as it is a starting pistol and doesn't have much in the way of armor penetration.


Maybe for balance it breaks it a little what with the CTs having a much better cheap AR in comparison to the T's Galil. Oh well! People seem to enjoy buying Deagles instead...I don't blame them.

I think that's it. I hope I covered everything someone would need before purchasing this game. In my opinion, it is the best CS title as of yet. The only problem I have, personally, is the fact it lacks a filter for, well...filtering OUT the community servers. But if that's not a problem to you, you should totally get this one. If it is, well...you're probably better off getting GO. 1.6 is essentially the same as Source though, uses a server browser, too. Doesn't even have Source's Tags feature, either.

CSS stands for Counter Strike Source (everyone knows), a Official Port/remake of Counter strike 1.6¬¥s Goldsrc engine to Source. As the First Game on Source engine. The Counter Strike Source impressed me for its time With it¬¥s features of support for DirectX 9 with lower down to DirectX 7 for slower Graphics Cards. This ensures you would get best Graphics at the time. CSS uses also updated Steam version , meaning it¬¥s alot harder to crack/pirate the game. The community is also nice i don¬¥t hear anyone screaming in the microphone like some singer. 8X MSAA Antialiasing makes textures look less blurry and helps you alot. The community has also zero tolerance against cheaters ,Meaning you will most likely found every server VAC Secured with additional Anti-Cheat like SourceMod Anti Cheat (not sponsored by). The game also takes it¬¥s core fun games from its predecessors like Bunnyhopping with custom modded stuff, Surf and Zombie Escape/survival.
For 10 euros i  can¬¥t complain and i can say only:
Get this game, Play this Game ,Enjoy this game.

This game is the perfect balance between fun and serious. You have maps that are designed for fun and others that are for serious.

 For example Ba_jail, in which one team plays as the cops and the others as prisoners. The prisoners have to do what the cops tell them to do or be killed, Now that isn't to say that you can't defy does orders and try to sneak away and get a gun to kill them with.

Zombies. We all know what this gamemode is. You try to survive for as long as possible, But there is also Zombie adventure maps, in which you have to get to the end of the map to win, unless you are a zombie.

Trikz. You might not now what this game mode is but it is real fun. 
This mode is all about teamwork, you cannot play this alone. So what you had to do was to boost your team up onto a platform by the means of a flashbang, yes a flashbang. If you didn't know you could throw a flashbang at your teamate as they were jumping over you to launch theme either straight up in the air or forward, if they were running.Once they are up on the platform they could open up a path for you and you redo it untill the end.

Gungame. We all know this mode aswell but if you don't for whatever reason i will explain.
You start with a pistol or which ever weapon that the host set it to. Every kill or every other kill gets you a new gun that you have to use to kill with. You do that untill you get the last gun, which usually is the knife.

There are more maps dedicated to those who just wanna play for fun, now i am not saying that you can't play a normal mode and have fun.

I just wanna say that it is sad how fast it died when Cs:go Came out and it is still pretty much dead to this day.

Si me preguntaran, ¬øCual es el mejor Counter strike? 
Counter Strike Source, esa seria mi respuesta. Recuerdo esa vez, alla por 2007, cuando entre al ciber y el primer juego que vi fue Counter Strike Source. Fue algo extra√±o, pues todos los chicos del ciber se la pasaban jugando al CS 1.6, absolutamente nadie jugaba al Counter Strike Source. Recuerdo haber pasado horas jugando este pezado de juego, fue uno de los primeros que experimente el Online.

Es lamentable que hasta su fecha, sea considerado un CS olvidado, junto al Condition Zero. Mucha gente prefiere esa cosa hecha de papel y carton al que llaman CS 1.6. 

Counter Strike Source en 2019 (se que aun no es a√±o nuevo pero seguro que cuando alguien lo lea sera ya 2019 lol) es un excelente titulo para recordar las viejas epocas de 2006 hasta 2010. En la actualidad consta con una comunidad algo activa, con una cantidad aceptable de jugadores. Hay mucha variedad de servidores, pero eso si, servidores vanilla, encontraras muy pocos. Antes, no se porque, el juego costaba 20 dolares! vete a joder! pero luego bajaron su precio. 

Pagar por su precio completo, que vendrian siendo como unos 9 dolares, me parece algo caro. Aun que haya dicho que encontraras personas jugando, realmente no te ofrece muchas horas de juego, al menos que encuentres amigos para jugarlo. Lo recomendaria si quieres alejarte de ese juego de papel de carton o simplemente no quieres jugar con una comunidad toxica y llena de hackers...

Very repetitive. You die, round restarts, you repeat the same thing: everyone gets stuck at same two bottlenecks on every map, maybe you kill a guy, but it gets tiresome quickly running to the same bottleneck over and over again getting shot with a single shot to the head when you leave the safety of your half of the map. Counter-strike fans loved the game (which is why they released CS:GO) but to anyone who didn't play the original 1000 hours and memorize all the maps, sniping spots, corners, and angles, this series is a rough one to acclimate to. 

Maps are incredibly basic looking. The horrible sound effects/techno music on some mods will constantly drive you to find a new server. But good luck, because 90% of all servers play only Dust (the desert map with all the ramps). Honestly, I only played this as a last resort because I got sick of TF2 and I got this free with HL2. Many better games out there to play. Insurgency is half the price, has far better mechanics, graphics, sounds, and maps.

i made a review for this game a few years ago but it was pretty bad so im going to remake that review and go more in-depth on this game.

Counter-strike: Source is a great game that not only showcases the capabilities of the source engine, but also what gamemodes and maps the community can create and share.

Story: Css doesn't have a story, but it doesn't need one to lure in players.

Gameplay: Css has your standard counter strike gameplay with a few changes that the source engine added.

Graphics: for the time, the graphics were great and they are not too bad these days.

Sound: the sound design was great for the time, and is not bad these days.

Multiplayer: This is the selling point of the game. The source engine brought with it alot of possibilities, and valve was handing out the sdk to everybody who wanted to make a map or a gamemode. This meant that there was alot of open room for creativity, and the community made good use of this. The community created TONS of gamemodes and custom maps such as jailbreak, bhop, surf, 24/7 deathmatch, and with the use of this game you can play Trouble in terrorist town in Gmod! There are way many more gamemodes that I didn't list but there is so much to play in the game that you can just host a server and play all these gamemodes with your friends.

Final Verdict: Counter-Strike: Source is a must play game that improved upon what made cs 1.6 so good and let the community go crazy with their own custom mods and maps.

Pros:
+A small yet dedicated community
+Realistic physics that are fun to play around with on maps like cs_office, in which you can 
  block doorways with cabinets and tables.

Cons:
-By small and dedicated I MEAN small and dedicated. compared to the other main CS games 
  this one has the least players playing at the same time. 3-4k compared with 1.6s 13-14k.
-Physic objects can sometimes block your way to the bomb / your way to the bombsite / your 
  way to the hostages so that provides an unfair advantage to one of the teams.
-Saw more cheaters here than on 1.6, no idea why tbh.

Yet it's still the best CS game in my opinion. 
Worth getting on the summer sale, but also worth its full price.

Words do not describe how much I love this game.

Even though I was born when CS:S was already out, I was introduced to it when I was young at a friends house.  I enjoyed watching those Flash Animations of the game, and watching just gameplay of it.  Then 2014 came along.  I finally had enough money to buy the game, and my first match was amazing.  To me, almost every gun is useable and has one pro that makes it useful.  Sadly though, the game is pretty dead if you're looking for a regular defusal map.  Most servers that are very populated are either: surf, bhop, or deathmatch/FFA.  I wish I was a bit older when CS:S first came out so I could've experienced what looked liked an amazing experience for so many people. But now, all I get to play is a game full of hackers, people who have played forever and refuse to by CS:GO, and little kids who bought CS:S for the textures for Garry's Mod.

[h1]WARNING: LONG REVIEW.[/h1]
Counter Strike: Source is quite possibly the Best and one of the earliest Games that i purchased here on steam. It's basically like the original Counter Strike but with the power of the source engine to revamp the game to give it some Pros, and quite many points of negativities.

First, lets start with the weapons. Like the Original CS 1.6, the Recoil is quite the same as from CSS. The difference i noticed that the original Deagle in CS 1.6 Takes 2 shots to shoot perfectly where the crosshair is pointed as-is. But in CSS, deagle takes only 1 shot to shoot perfectly. Next shots (2- 7 shots) will make it inaccurate. I like this feauture. But it's so overpowered i get fragged at T-Spawn in de_dust2 by only one shot with the Deagle. At the first round. So it's 50-50% that i hate/love this feature. AK-47 fires the same as in CS 1.6, no problem with that.

Ah, yes. The Source Engine‚Ñ¢. How could i forget. Half-Life 2's revoloutionary Source engine, combined with CS 1.6 is quite amazing. Better graphics, features, ect etc etc etc. It somehow amazing, the VALVe‚Ñ¢ formula works.

Third, the Bots. Good thing VALVe‚Ñ¢ Added Bots. Those bots are my best friends [spoilers]Or enemies[/spoilers] when there's no Intenet Connnection. Bad thing is, these bots seemed like the AI is ported over from CS;CZ, which sucks. Ally bot AI is catastrophic. Bots block your way when they get idle, this is worse when they do this at de_dust2's Suicide path. And it makes you go to path Outside Long just to get to Mid/catwalk because Bots block your way. And that sucks ALOT. 

TL;DR:

Recoil with deagle:
[table]
   [tr]
[th]CS1.6[/th]
[th]CSS[/th]
[/tr]
[tr]
[td]2 Shots to be accurate[/td]
[td]1 shot to be accurate[/td]
[/tr]
[/table]

Nonetheless, i still Like CSS. It's infact one of the reasons Steam‚Ñ¢ is getting bigger than it was the other day.


7/10

Counter-Strike: Source is effectively Counter-Strike: Global Offensive, but without the infamous "CS:GO Ballstink." 

CS:GO Ballstink is a common disorder among CS:GO players wherein their testicles become smelly in a statistically significant manner. This is often attributed to the overwhelming and omnipresent "try-hard" personality which manifests in long-time CS:GO players. 

This game, with its smaller player-base, avoids the ballstink pitfall, as there is a general comradery among the players, and thus toxic interactions are less frequent.

Also, this game's knife is objectively uglier than the ones in CS:GO, but that keeps all the traders away, so it is a plus.

My invitation to the Counter-Strike games were through CS: Source, when my friend would show me him sniping noobs, back in the days of bulky computer monitors, nearly reaching their peak (it was like 2006/2007), I can vaguely remember taking turns each game (since dying was easy to do in the game, at least for me), so when I found this on offer, I had to buy it!

There isn't a vast majority of weapon choices, unlike games such as Call of Duty or Battlefield, but that doesn't mean they are bad choices. They are definitely practical and you find yourself getting good at using weapons that you didn't even use before, simply due to this limitation, There is also a buy menu in most games, which is a pretty unique feature for games like this, as it makes the player learn to adapt with what he/she can get. However, I tend to join servers that allow you to spawn with a random primary weapon, simply because it is easier when you want a quick match.

If you're familiar with the Source Engine or the Half-Life series, then I would recommend looking this up! BOOM, HEADSHOT! 95/100!

[h1] Der Klassiker des Shooter Genres in Neuauflage[/h1]

Zu [i]Counter-Strike[/i] (CS) muss man eigentlich nicht mehr viel sagen - das Spiel ist eines der bekanntesten und ber√ºchtigtsten Videospiele allerzeiten und [u]der Klassiker[/u] des First Person Shooter Genres. Bereits der erste Teil der Spielereihe, CS 1.6, setzte den Standard f√ºr das Genre und ist wohl einer der meistgespielten Multiplayer Shooter √ºberhaupt. [i]Counter-Strike[/i] ist so simpel wie genial: Das einfache Spielprinzip, zwei Teams die sich gegenseitig ausschalten oder Missionsziele erreichen/verhindern m√ºssen, macht einfach nur unglaublich viel Spa√ü, insbesondere mit Freunden. Das Spiel ist einfach ein Skill-Shooter ohne viel √ºberfl√ºssige  Action, bei welchem es alleine auf die F√§higkeiten des einzelnen Spielers ankommt.

[i]Counter-Strike: Source[/i] nimmt das geniale Spielprinzip seines Vorg√§ngers und setzt es mittels der fortschrittlichen [i]Source[/i]-Engine auf ein ganz neues grafisches Niveau. Im Vergleich zu CS 1.6 ist dieser Teil grafisch ein ganz neues Level und die Physik der [i]Source[/i]-Engine macht das Spiel noch ein ganzes St√ºck realistischer.

Auch wenn mittlerweile [i]Counter-Strike: Global Offensive[/i] der neue Standard bei den Multiplayer Taktik-Shootern ist, so ist CS:S keinesfalls tot: Immer noch h√§lt eine Fan-Community dem Spiel die Treue und besonders f√ºr Nostalgiker wie mich, die das Spiel noch von fr√ºher kennen, ist es immer wieder eine sch√∂ne Sache es mit Freunden zusammen zu spielen.

Been playing for 5 years in a row. Honestly, best game I've ever played!

As a super fan of first-person shooter, the graphic of this game is extremely simple and easy to get used to. In this modern time when every current FPS game like CSGO is now 3D and has fancy effects, this game is not one of those. Although the graphic sometimes feels rough or cheesy, but this game can be literally running in any device because it doesn't need a high-tech CPU to run these graphics. If you have a friend you want to play with, as long as he has a common computer even an office laptop you can still do it. I play Multigames and Zombie Escape server a lot where people can freely make their own maps and servers. Some ZE maps are very epic and they even have stories or are based on a movie. The physics work mostly pretty well and the effects are acceptable. If you are looking forward to Counter-Strike simple competitive, this game might not be for you because this is very entertaining. For something you can do differently in CSS rather than CSGO, you can go to gamebanana.com to download your own weapon skins. In all servers it has much more commands like mute teammates' shooting sound. I really hope more people can be into this game. Although it is an old game, it's NOT LATE at all to get started.

CS: Source is the best game to play for when you don't want to stress yourself playing an exhausting and demanding fps shooter but you still want to experience the fun of that genre. This game is pretty easy, smooth to play and doesn't require your highest concentration. After work, sometimes you're just tired and want to play a fun, relaxing game, that's CS: Source for you!

With various gamemodes you can lay back and play things like Zombie Escape, Zombie Mode, bhop, surf, Jailbreak, $2000$ or the intended Search & Destroy type of match. It doesn't consume much of your time, you can just start the game and jump right in and it's pretty forgiving. You can play without even trying and still win. Good aim and movement are required to be the best player. This game is by the book the definition of an fps multiplayer shooter and most gamers feel at home with this Counter-Strike.

[h1] Un Counter Strike diferente [/h1]
 Counter Strike Source fue un juego graficamemte adelantado de su tiempo, cosa que supuso una bendicion y tambien una maldicion, ya que por una parte envejecio relativamente bien pero por el otro lado hizo que en el momemto de lanzamiento mucha gente no estuvo dispuesta a comprar una nueva computadora solo para jugar este titulo, lo que hizo uno de los juegos mas impopulares de la saga.
Hoy en d√≠a es un juego que recomemdaria si estas cansado de Csgo y quieres probar algo similar pero de otra epoca con otro enfoque. Si vienes de csgo se te sera relativamente mas facil acostumbrarte a alguien que venga de cs 1.6 por ejemplo debido a que a ellos se les sera un poco mas complejo adaptarse a los graficos y a la configuracion de las armas. Pero al final de cuentas es un juego que recomiendo para todo fan de los fps por lo bien que ha envejecido, por su calidad y por la fiel comunidad aun activa.

Despite it saying I only played for half an hour, I grew up on this game. It's probably somewhere closer to 300 or 400. Always good for a dose of nostalgic deathmatch.

[h1] Counter-Strike: Source [/h1]

[b] A Decent Shooter Nowadays, If A Bit Jarring To Play [/b]

[b] Counter Strike: Source [/b] is nearly 15 years old, and yet still has some pretty good physics and gameplay for a multiplayer FPS title. The servers aren't very populated, but it is still possible to get into a lobby for a somewhat normal match, or even for a gun-game type of match. 

The visuals are dated compared to  modern game of course, but they look pretty good for a 2004 title. The gunplay is nice and responsive, and the audio is crisp and pretty loud at times, drawing you into the game even more. 

The physics system is different than the original [b] Counter-Strike [/b], which is nice at times with some fights. I've never really been a fan of CS grenades, so I can't really give an honest evaluation of the system for those since I am a bit biased against them. They're just "meh" to me, but serve their purpose at times. As for maps and guns, a lot are taken from the OG title, so not much has really changed here.

Honestly, the game is sort of dead at this point. Yes there are still some servers and players, so you can get some enjoyment out of this one, but it won't really be the intended experience at all. I can still [b] Recommend [/b] the game since it is cheap and fun for a bit, but it isn't a very highly recommended title. I would play this one over the original unless you really enjoy the feel of that title, but CSGO is more modern and populated so that players can experience the game in a more natural setting.

[h2] Final Verdict: 5/10 (Average) [/h2]

Bueno esta es la tercera entrega de la saga cs despues del condition cero y quiero aclarar que es el mejor cs que se ha hecho,tal vez el cs go tenga mejores graficas pero sin duda este le supera en todos los apartados xD y a continuacion les mostrare mis opiniones.

Jugabilidad:
Sin duda mejoraron muchas cosas desde el cs 1.6,su control es un poco mejor que el anterior y su manejo y apunte en las armas esta sin duda muy mejorado en cada detalle

Graficas:
Bueno lo logico es que cambiaran las graficas, las armas estan muy bien detalladas y se nota el esfuerzo de conseguir que el espectador alucine con las armas,tambien arreglaron esos bug y fallos de texturas en rincones y objetos del mapa.

Sonido:
Muy realista el sonido y muy logrado para que el espectador sienta como si el mismo estuviera disparando en la vida real,sobre todo arreglaron un fallo que habia en el sonido que era un poco agudo el sonido al disparar pero ahora ya no pasa ese fallo.

Innovacion:
Bueno a decir verdad no han cambiado los mapas pero no pasa nada, lo que querian era que recordaramos esos mapas y esos recuerdos en cs 1.6
pero si quereis ver otros mapas,en algunos servidores hay nuevos mapas y por pura suerte siguen haciendo nuevos mapas para que no nos cansemos.

Se nota que Valve se esfuerza mucho en sus juegos y que escucha nuestras ideas para mejoras sus juegos,sin duda le doy un 10 por ser uno de los mejores juegos online de la historia.

While CSS and CSGO are both great games and I don't see no reason as to why you shouldn't buy Counter Strike Source, I would like to point out the pros and cons of CSS (At least based on MY thoughts and preferences) while comparing it with CSGO to help you decide which one you should buy.

Pros:
1.Lets get this one out of the way. Definitely feels way more fun than CSGO in general.
2.Gunplay plays out smoother and the recoil of the weapons plays a big part on that. (CSS has random recoil while CSGO has preset recoil for each weapon)
3.Customizable...A LOT. With a little basic knowledge of the engine, you can add your own custom models, materials, sounds, etc etc. And even some new modes using sourcemod or other plugins. (Sure as hell beats CSGO's skins, which are paid...)
4.More variety on custom servers (DM, Surf, Zombie, Zombie escape, etc)
5.Its rather more casual than competitive, which is what I prefer.
6.Better bots (In my opinion and experience)
7.Less toxic community (Including kids, russians etc), but that doesn't mean its toxic free! (All the wankers moved on to CSGO)
8.You can tweak your server settings when starting a map, rather than starting a match with preset settings, and having to fiddle with the console.
9.Hitboxes, while they are a bit big and got some complaints, I feel like they fit right in the game and are way more responsive than CSGO's hitboxes.
10.Snipers feel damn fine to use in this game
11.No CZ 75, No R8, No Mag 7, No Sawn off, No negev, No tec 9 etc etc. CSS has the original weapons from CS 1.6 and thats it. (This includes the fact that there is one M4, instead of CSGO, which has 2)
12.Guns are tweaked just about right. Each one feels balanced and deserves the stats that it has.Not too OP, and not too shit. Yeah, even the glock, believe it or not.
13.Suprisingly, less hackers.
14.I think the maps in CSS are more fun to play, rather than CSGO variants.
15.Gamebanana and other sites have a gigantic collection of custom maps for the game.
16.No weapon skins. (Instead you can get a buttload of cool custom models and reskins)

Cons:
1.Less active community than CSGO.
2.Servers with "premium" features (Only Premium users have access to AWP, Auto sniper, have 150 health etc etc) are common.
3.No official servers like CSGO. (Most servers will be in a way or another, modified and not vanilla, at least the ones with players in it)
4.66 tick servers.
5.Graphics are a bit dated.
6.No lobby system.
7.No matchmaking.
8.Hostages can be killed, which can lead to exploits (Although hostage killers do get punished so its not common to kill hostages)
9.Wallbanging is drastically reduced and less effective

In conclusion, I think Counter Strike Source is a better game than CSGO. Hell! I think its the best in the series.
If you're a casual player like me, you should get this. If you like competitive, I think CSGO is your choice (Although you can find clans who host competitive matches in CSS, which are awesome)

Adolf Hitler was a German politician who was the leader of the Nazi Party (Nationalsozialistische Deutsche Arbeiterpartei; NSDAP), Chancellor of Germany from 1933 to 1945, and F√ºhrer ("leader") of Nazi Germany from 1934 to 1945. As dictator of Nazi Germany, he initiated World War II in Europe with the invasion of Poland in September 1939 and was a central figure of the Holocaust.

Hitler was born into a German-speaking Austrian family and raised near Linz. He moved to Germany in 1913 and was decorated during his service in the German Army in World War I. He joined the German Workers' Party, the precursor of the NSDAP, in 1919 and became leader of the NSDAP in 1921. In 1923, he attempted a coup in Munich to seize power. The failed coup resulted in Hitler's imprisonment, during which time he dictated the first volume of his autobiography and political manifesto Mein Kampf ("My Struggle"). After his release in 1924, Hitler gained popular support by attacking the Treaty of Versailles and promoting Pan-Germanism, anti-Semitism, and anti-communism with charismatic oratory and Nazi propaganda. Hitler frequently denounced international capitalism and communism as being part of a Jewish conspiracy.

By 1933, the Nazi Party was the largest elected party in the German Reichstag, which led to Hitler's appointment as Chancellor on 30 January 1933. Following fresh elections won by his coalition, the Reichstag passed the Enabling Act, which began the process of transforming the Weimar Republic into Nazi Germany, a one-party dictatorship based on the totalitarian and autocratic ideology of National Socialism. Hitler aimed to eliminate Jews from Germany and establish a New Order to counter what he saw as the injustice of the post-World War I international order dominated by Britain and France. His first six years in power resulted in rapid economic recovery from the Great Depression, the effective abandonment of restrictions imposed on Germany after World War I, and the annexation of territories that were home to millions of ethnic Germans‚Äîactions which gave him significant popular support.

Hitler sought Lebensraum ("living space") for the German people. His aggressive foreign policy is considered to be the primary cause of the outbreak of World War II in Europe. He directed large-scale rearmament and on 1 September 1939 invaded Poland, resulting in British and French declarations of war on Germany. In June 1941, Hitler ordered an invasion of the Soviet Union. By the end of 1941 German forces and the European Axis powers occupied most of Europe and North Africa. Failure to defeat the Soviets and the entry of the United States into the war forced Germany onto the defensive and it suffered a series of escalating defeats. In the final days of the war, during the Battle of Berlin in 1945, Hitler married his long-time lover, Eva Braun. On 30 April 1945, less than two days later, the two killed themselves to avoid capture by the Red Army, and their corpses were burned.

Under Hitler's leadership and racially motivated ideology, the Nazi regime was responsible for the genocide of at least 5.5 million Jews and millions of other victims whom he and his followers deemed Untermenschen ("sub-humans") and socially undesirable. Hitler and the Nazi regime were also responsible for the killing of an estimated 19.3 million civilians and prisoners of war. In addition, 29 million soldiers and civilians died as a result of military action in the European Theatre of World War II. The number of civilians killed during the Second World War was unprecedented in warfare, and constitutes the deadliest conflict in human history.

If by now you have not played a Counter-Strike game, it might be time to. It is a great FPS, that has a single and multiplayer aspect. The single player being, playing against bots that are of a certain difficuly, and the multiplayer being against other players. Depending on the map that is chosen, depends on the what the opjectives are. There are 2 teams against each other, one being Terrorists, and the other being Counter-terrorists. If the map has a prefix of 'de', it is a bomb map. Bomb maps being that the terrorist plant a bomb and the counter-terrosits defuse it once it has been planted. The maps with a 'cs' prefix, are hostage based. Terrorists protect the hostages from being taken back, and the counter-terrorits try to get them back. All maps can be won by eliminating the entire other team. At the beginning of every round, you are able to buy your weapon of choice and grenades to go with it, so long as you have the money to do so. To get money, win rounds, plant/defuse bombs or rescue hostages, and kill your opponents. Kill teammates to lose money and get a round suspention (if friendly fire is on).
All and all, an awesome game to just have a quick round or two, or spend hours farming achievements and killing enemys and friends alike. (friends being on your steam list on the other team ofcourse)

Two sets of objectives exist in CS: rescue or defend a group of hostages, or bomb and defend sites of historical importance. Killing the enemy, or completing your objectives, nets you cash, to be spent on deadlier weapons, Kevlar armour and matching earmuffs, grenades, defusing kits, nightvision goggles, and every accessory for the fashion conscious 21st century digital warrior. Half-Life T and integrated voice-chat technology have added to the social experience. For progamers it's less a game, more a way of life.

[h1][b][u]Counter-Strike: Source[/u][/b][/h1]

[b]Pros of the game:[/b]
[list]
[*] Better updated graphics and content to the original.

[*] Improved weapon mechanics and performance.

[*] Better player movement and reaction rendering.

[*] More expansive map remakes and community map content added.

[*] A lot of fun to play with friends as well as nice community players you‚Äôd meet in various servers.

[*] Quite a large percentage of users still play it to date, regardless of being a number of years old.

[*] The community-modded ‚ÄòGun Game‚Äô and ‚ÄòSurf‚Äô servers, to change up the usual notion of gaming, as well as 'Z-mod' listings.

[*] Achievements and recorded lifetime game play stats can help as a reference base to sharpen skills as a perfectionist, as well as improving general performance for others.

[*] Awesome fun to have been involved in professional sponsored league matches for over my prior gaming career, and still doesn't get old to enjoy an occasional round or two over for recreation.
[/list]

[b]Cons of the game:[/b]
[list]
[*] The 'Clan Warfare' achievement, as not everyone plays in professional leagues or with teams with that many players to have the same team tags.

[*] Lifetime game play statistics still being recorded in offline single-player matches with bots, instead of containing it solely to actual multi-player matches online.

[*] The lifetime statistics themselves can be a bit of a burden for people wanting to keep quite a good performance constantly in check, with being a perfectionist as myself for example.

[*] Game play is not as simplified as back in the first version, adding a tad more complexity for beginners.

[*] An increased population of trolls and abusive players who can potentially disrupt enjoying matches, compared to the first game.

[*] A slight number of hit-box issues where blood-spatter renders on enemies, yet no damage is inflicted - or to a much lesser extent than an actual registered wound would give.
[/list]

[b]Personal feedback rating:[/b] 9.5 out of 10.

-Los que quedaron fascinados eligiendo a CS: S como su juego principal
-Los que segu√≠an jugando al Counter-Strike cl√°sico, ya que la jugabilidad competitiva era mejor y los torneos eran desarrollados en este t√≠tulo.

Pese a todos los aspectos negativos que algunos usuarios vean en este juego en lo personal me parece muy divertido y un buen t√≠tulo, que no est√° muerto ya que en servidores no oficiales puedes encontrar mucha gente, aunque lo m√°s √≥ptimo es comprar el juego original y ya teniendo el t√≠tulo conectarse a servidores comunitarios, hay que promover la no pirater√≠a.

Counter-Strike Source is a game we all know and love. Counter-Strike Source is the base of what everyone loves about CS:GO, but it has it's own feel to it. The 1990's Source Engine models, gameplay, etc. are what give this game to me an authentic computer game vibe. When you say FPS, many people including myself will automatically think "Counter-Strike!" The game itself is basic. You have terrorists. You have counter-terrorists. The terrorists are to plant and explode a bomb. The counter-terrorists are supposed to prevent them from doing that. Simple. Even though this is the most basic gametype in Counter-Stike, there are many other things to do in the game like surfing, hostage rescue, deathmatch, and many more. If you're a die-hard Valve fan or CS:GO fan, I highly recommend this staple in PC gaming history...

Following the line of the Counter-Strike series, this is the third offical game in the series. After the success of the first one, there was a time gap until 2004, when both Counter-Strike Source and Counter-Strike Condition Zero released. This was a long awaited sequel, however, many people were left disapointed, and a lot of the previous Counter-Strike players left this to continue on with the original. But, this sparked another life in this game, and were picked up by many; at the time young people. Even though this game wasn't at all as big in the competetive scene as the previous, it appealed more to new players, and helped the franchise to grow. Not as successfull, nor as good as the original, but still a great game.

TL;DR
Still some life left in this game, however this game is along with it's big brother, quite dead.

Overall score, 8/10

I decided to buy it to support Valve. This game is a bit my nostalgia for CS even though I played it very late. The graphics are very good for a game released in 2004 and the game is very easy to use. What I prefer and that I have always preferred is the community aspect of Valve games and especially this CSS! You can create maps for free and easily thanks to Hammer which is usable even without the game for free. The maps can then be used on community servers which makes the shooter we all know an almost endless playground! You can do surf, deathrun, deathmatch, surf deathmatch, ba_jail, mini games, a bomb scenario or a hostage! This game will forever remain in my heart in the unseen to video games.

The date of the start of the history of the United States is a subject of debate among historians. Older textbooks start with the arrival of Christopher Columbus on October 12, 1492 and emphasize the European background, or they start around 1600 and emphasize the American frontier. In recent decades American schools and universities typically have shifted back in time to include more on the colonial period and much more on the prehistory of the Native peoples.[1][2]

Indigenous people lived in what is now the United States for thousands of years before European colonists began to arrive, mostly from England, after 1600. The Spanish had small settlements in Florida and the Southwest, and the French along the Mississippi River and the Gulf Coast. By the 1770s, thirteen British colonies contained two and a half million people along the Atlantic coast east of the Appalachian Mountains. In the 1760s, the British government imposed a series of new taxes while rejecting the American argument that any new taxes had to be approved by the people (see Stamp Act 1765). Tax resistance, especially the Boston Tea Party (1774), led to punitive laws (the Intolerable Acts) by Parliament designed to end self-government in Massachusetts. American Patriots (as they called themselves) adhered to a political ideology called republicanism that emphasized civic duty, virtue, and opposition to corruption, fancy luxuries and aristocracy.

Armed conflict began in 1775 as Patriots drove the royal officials out of every colony and assembled in mass meetings and conventions. In 1776, the Second Continental Congress declared that there was a new, independent nation, the United States of America, not just a collection of disparate colonies. With large-scale military and financial support from France and military leadership by General George Washington, the American Patriots won the Revolutionary War.

The peace treaty of 1783 gave the new nation the land east of the Mississippi River (except Florida and Canada). The central government established by the Articles of Confederation proved ineffectual at providing stability, as it had no authority to collect taxes and had no executive officer. Congress called a convention to meet secretly in Philadelphia in 1787. It wrote a new Constitution, which was adopted in 1789. In 1791, a Bill of Rights was added to guarantee inalienable rights. With Washington as the first president and Alexander Hamilton his chief political and financial adviser, a strong central government was created. When Thomas Jefferson became president he purchased the Louisiana Territory from France, doubling the size of the United States. A second and final war with Britain was fought in 1812.

Encouraged by the notion of Manifest Destiny, federal territory expanded all the way to the Pacific. The U.S. always was large in terms of area, but its population was small, only 4 million in 1790. Population growth was rapid, reaching 7.2 million in 1810, 32 million in 1860, 76 million in 1900, 132 million in 1940, and 321 million in 2015. Economic growth in terms of overall GDP was even faster. However the nation's military strength was quite limited in peacetime before 1940. The expansion was driven by a quest for inexpensive land for yeoman farmers and slave owners. The expansion of slavery was increasingly controversial and fueled political and constitutional battles, which were resolved by compromises. Slavery was abolished in all states north of the Mason‚ÄìDixon line by 1804, but the South continued to profit off the institution, producing high-value cotton exports to feed increasing high demand in Europe. The 1860 presidential election of Republican Abraham Lincoln was on a platform of ending the expansion of slavery and putting it on a path to extinction.

Seven cotton-based deep South slave states seceded and later founded the Confederacy months before Lincoln's inauguration. No nation ever recognized the Confederacy, but it opened the war by attacking Fort Sumter in 1861. A surge of nationalist outrage in the North fueled a long, intense American Civil War (1861-1865). It was fought largely in the South as the overwhelming material and manpower advantages of the North proved decisive in a long war. The war's result was restoration of the Union, the impoverishment of the South, and the abolition of slavery. In the Reconstruction era (1863‚Äì1877), legal and voting rights were extended to the freed slave. The national government emerged much stronger, and because of the Fourteenth Amendment in 1868, it gained the explicit duty to protect individual rights. However, when white Democrats regained their power in the South during the 1870s, often by paramilitary suppression of voting, they passed Jim Crow laws to maintain white supremacy, and new disfranchising constitutions that prevented most African Americans and many poor whites from voting, a situation that continued for decades until gains of the civil rights movement in the 1960s and passage of federal legislation to enforce constitutional rights.

The United States became the world's leading industrial power at the turn of the 20th century due to an outburst of entrepreneurship in the Northeast and Midwest and the arrival of millions of immigrant workers and farmers from Europe. The national railroad network was completed with the work of Chinese immigrants and large-scale mining and factories industrialized the Northeast and Midwest. Mass dissatisfaction with corruption, inefficiency and traditional politics stimulated the Progressive movement, from the 1890s to 1920s, which led to many social and political reforms. In 1920, the 19th Amendment to the Constitution guaranteed women's suffrage (right to vote). This followed the 16th and 17th amendments in 1913, which established the first national income tax and direct election of US senators to Congress. Initially neutral during World War I, the US declared war on Germany in 1917 and later funded the Allied victory the following year.

After a prosperous decade in the 1920s, the Wall Street Crash of 1929 marked the onset of the decade-long worldwide Great Depression. Democratic President Franklin D. Roosevelt ended the Republican dominance of the White House and implemented his New Deal programs for relief, recovery, and reform. The New Deal, which defined modern American liberalism, included relief for the unemployed, support for farmers, Social Security and a minimum wage. The United States and the Soviet Union emerged as rival superpowers after World War II. During the Cold War, the US and the USSR confronted each other indirectly in the arms race, the Space Race, proxy wars, and propaganda campaigns. RIP Counter Strike. A loved game killed in 2012 by the shit fest known as Global Offensive.

This game was everything in my childhood, and is still a classic now with many players still in ALL game styles.

Let me try and break this down best I can to give you wonderful people of the Steam Community EVERY reason to buy this game:

First off, let's talk about the million-and-one game modes you can play. Normal, bhop, surf, zriot, ze, zm, hideandseek, mg, hoejus,, fy, gungame, scoutsknives, awpknives etc. - which were all community made including the maps, with NO EXTRA COST! Just head on into the server browser, and enjoy.

Next, let's talk about how the community is far from toxic. If we look at CSGO currently (whether it's casual or competitive, at whatever ranking stage) - there is always one who wants to be billy big b0ll0cks and talk smack to everyone else, or be loud, grief etc etc. In this, there are still... Wait for it...

DEDICATED SERVERS! Admins can mute, kill, kick and ban this minority, leaving you to get on with the fun.

If you're not one of these people who want to play the many different game modes offered in this, and still want good, olf-fashioned hostage or bomb Counter Strike, not to worry - it's still there! Only you don't have to pay monthly or sign up to a website to have the option to play 128 tick servers - that's the norm for this game *cough* 64tick CSGO *cough*

Overall, I have had MANY hours of entertainment (and still do), I've met many friends whom are now very close and even travelled to different countries to meet them, and I do, have, and always will recommend this Counter Strike to absolutely anybody.

Thanks for reading! Happy gaming. :) :)
